Livingstone Hospital social workers are desperately searching or the relatives of a man who was brought to the hospital by ambulance on Monday afternoon. Picture: Supplied Social workers at Livingstone Hospital are looking for the relatives of a man who was brought to the hospital by ambulance on Monday afternoon. Social worker Neliswa Siwisa said: He was picked up by an ambulance near Provincial Hospital and brought to Livingstone Hospital. He is unable to speak or write. We suspect he had a stroke. Siwisa added that the man looked to be in his late 40s or early 50s. We are desperately looking for his family, she said Anybody who knows the man s identity or his family can phone Siwisa on 0827343902. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share